### 5.1 Agent 1: Compliance Agent
**File:** [compliance-agent/main.py](file:///Users/utkarshsingh/Desktop/Trinetra/agents/compliance-agent/main.py)
**Current lines:** 101

#### What to add:
After the compliance check (line 94), store the result in Actian and query for prior submissions from the same PAN.

```python
# Add to imports (top of file):
from shared.vectorai_client import VectorAIClient
vectorai = VectorAIClient()

# Add INSIDE process(), after computing the result (before return):

# ── Actian VectorAI: Store compliance result ──
pan = ucso.get("applicant", {}).get("pan", "")
company = ucso.get("applicant", {}).get("company_name", "")
compliance_text = f"Compliance check for {company} (PAN: {pan}). Status: {'PASS' if not missing else 'FAIL'}. Missing: {missing}"
vectorai.upsert(
    collection="application_summaries",
    doc_id=f"{application_id}_compliance",
    text=compliance_text,
    metadata={
        "application_id": application_id,
        "pan": pan,
        "agent": "compliance-agent",
        "status": "PASS" if not missing else "FAIL",
        "phase": "compliance",
    }
)

# ── Actian VectorAI: Check for prior applications from same PAN ──
if pan:
    prior = vectorai.hybrid_search(
        collection="application_summaries",
        query_text=f"compliance check PAN {pan}",
        filters={"pan": pan, "phase": "compliance"},
        top_k=3,
    )
    if len(prior) > 1:  # More than just this one
        self.logger.info(f"Found {len(prior)-1} prior applications from PAN {pan}")
