## 7. Collection Seeding Script

### [NEW] `agents/seed_vectorai.py`

Seeds the Actian VectorAI collections with sample data (news, litigation, RBI circulars, MCA filings) so the Web Agent and MCA Agent have data to query on first run.

```python
"""Seed Actian VectorAI with sample financial intelligence data."""
from shared.vectorai_client import VectorAIClient

vectorai = VectorAIClient()

# Create all collections
COLLECTIONS = [
    "document_chunks", "financial_profiles", "gst_patterns",
    "bank_recon_profiles", "news_articles", "litigation_records",
    "rbi_circulars", "mca_filings", "pan_profiles", "risk_decisions",
    "pd_transcripts", "stress_scenarios", "audit_events", "application_summaries",
]
for name in COLLECTIONS:
    vectorai.create_collection(name)
    print(f"  ✅ Created collection: {name}")

# Seed news_articles with sample Indian business news
SAMPLE_NEWS = [
    {"id": "news_001", "text": "Adani Group reports strong revenue growth of 45% YoY", "metadata": {"headline": "Adani Group reports strong revenue growth", "source_url": "https://example.com", "credibility_score": 4, "published_at": "2026-03-15T00:00:00Z"}},
    {"id": "news_002", "text": "SEBI investigation into circular trading at mid-cap firms", "metadata": {"headline": "SEBI probes circular trading", "source_url": "https://example.com", "credibility_score": 5, "published_at": "2026-04-01T00:00:00Z"}},
    # ... add 20-30 more sample articles
]
vectorai.upsert_batch("news_articles", SAMPLE_NEWS)

# Seed rbi_circulars, litigation_records, mca_filings similarly...
print("🎉 Seeding complete!")
```

